name: Schools free breakfast clubs
summary: The government has recently announced that 750 schools will be offered free breakfast clubs to tackle childhood hunger. The move is part of a wider initiative to provide support to children in deprived areas. The breakfast clubs will be provided to schools in England and Scotland, with over 50 schools in the North East confirmed to receive the funding. The clubs will save parents an estimated £450 per year and will be used to justify keeping the two-child benefits cap. The government has also published a list of the schools that will be receiving the funding, which can be found on the GOV.UK website.

name: Everton vs Man United
summary: Everton and Manchester United played out an entertaining 2-2 draw in the Premier League at Goodison Park. Everton took an early lead through Alex Iwobi, but Manchester United responded with goals from Antony and Cristiano Ronaldo. Demarai Gray equalized for Everton in the second half, but the hosts were denied a late penalty. The result leaves Everton in 11th place in the standings, while Manchester United remain in fifth.

name: Bivol
summary: In a highly anticipated rematch, Dmitry Bivol defeated Artur Beterbiev via majority decision points, capturing Beterbiev's undisputed light heavyweight crown. The classic battle took place in Riyadh, Saudi Arabia, and saw Bivol once again outmaneuver and outbox his opponent. The victory leaves the boxing world torn, as both fighters displayed exceptional skills and determination. The event also featured a matchup between Joe Parker and Junior Bakole, adding to the excitement of the evening.
